        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3333706533" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10154143111178216704"><b>*** 3.65 ***</b><br/><br/>There is a real promise of a good storyteller here, but it being his first book, I can forgive many of the inconsistencies both in world building and language. I appreciate the different view of the magical creatures of legend and the idea of them moving to a different continent - From the British Isles during Empire time, to the New Continent - the Americas... However, as much as i love the idea behind the premise, the execution really needs some work. Still, I enjoyed the story eno</span>
  <span id="freeText10154143111178216704" style="display:none"><b>*** 3.65 ***</b><br /><br />There is a real promise of a good storyteller here, but it being his first book, I can forgive many of the inconsistencies both in world building and language. I appreciate the different view of the magical creatures of legend and the idea of them moving to a different continent - From the British Isles during Empire time, to the New Continent - the Americas... However, as much as i love the idea behind the premise, the execution really needs some work. Still, I enjoyed the story enough to want to see where the trilogy goes with it:) </span>
